The Poly-Crisis, refers to the convergence and interaction of multiple global crises occurring simultaneously, each exacerbating the others. These crises span various domains including environmental, economic, social, political, and technological spheres. The poly-crisis is characterized by its complexity, interconnectedness, and the way these multiple crises compound and amplify each other.  
